.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-BLRULES 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-blrules \- blacklist rules with full rule grammar for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I blrules
file provides blacklisting with the full rule grammar: action, source,
destination, protocol, and port filtering.  Unlike the simpler
.I blacklist
file (which only lists source addresses),
.I blrules
lets you blacklist based on any combination of source and destination.

The compiler processes this file separately from
.I rules
and emits the resulting nft rules early in the zone-pair chains, before
the main rules are evaluated.  Rules support
.B ?SECTION
grouping (same as
.IR rules ).

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/blrules
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	DROP, REJECT, or WHITELIST
SOURCE	yes	Source zone:address or CIDR
DEST	yes	Destination zone:address or CIDR
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Drop traffic from a known-bad network to the DMZ:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  SOURCE              DEST   PROTO  DPORT
DROP     net:198.51.100.0/24 dmz
.fi
.RE
.PP
Reject inbound SSH from specific subnets:
.RS
.nf
REJECT   net:203.0.113.0/24  fw     tcp    22
.fi
.RE
.PP
Whitelist a trusted host from the global block:
.RS
.nf
WHITELIST net:198.51.100.1   fw
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-blacklist (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

